WEBVTT

00:01.420 --> 00:02.924
<i>Kids, Stella Zenman was the girl</i>

00:03.285 --> 00:04.889
<i>I thought I'd spend
the rest of my life with.</i>

00:05.892 --> 00:07.596
<i>Until she left me at the altar,</i>

00:07.596 --> 00:09.842
<i>smashing my heart
to smithereens.</i>

00:09.842 --> 00:11.176
<i>So when I ran into her
seven months later,</i>

00:11.176 --> 00:14.054
<i>there was only one way
to deal with her.</i>

00:14.054 --> 00:15.818
Stella!

00:16.460 --> 00:17.463
Great to see you!

00:17.463 --> 00:18.495
You, too.

00:18.495 --> 00:19.869
And Tony!

00:19.869 --> 00:21.804
Hey.
Hey!

00:21.804 --> 00:23.378
What a nice surprise.

00:23.378 --> 00:25.112
"What a nice surprise"?

00:25.112 --> 00:27.819
No, a nice surprise
would be if a safe fell

00:27.819 --> 00:29.825
from 40 stories
and smushed them both.

00:29.825 --> 00:31.459
I mean, you didn't
let them have it?

00:31.459 --> 00:33.063
No, we had a nice
friendly chat,

00:33.063 --> 00:35.109
then they went their
way and I went mine.

00:35.109 --> 00:36.211
Ted, you blew it.

00:36.211 --> 00:37.545
He blew it, right?

00:39.420 --> 00:40.583
Well played, sir.

00:40.583 --> 00:41.526
Bravo.

00:41.526 --> 00:42.990
What?!
You see, Robin,

00:42.990 --> 00:44.364
Ted played it cool,

00:44.364 --> 00:46.469
which is exactly what
he should have done.

00:46.469 --> 00:49.306
As a matter of fact, I'd say
on a scale ranging from...

00:49.306 --> 00:51.482
(sobbing):
And I kept this sweater
of yours...

00:52.384 --> 00:54.791
...and sometimes I just
sit in the bathtub

00:54.791 --> 00:58.571
for hours just, you know,
just sniffing it.

00:58.571 --> 01:00.075
...all the way to...

01:00.075 --> 01:01.940
This is my new fianc?.

01:01.940 --> 01:03.343
She's basically Stella,

01:03.343 --> 01:04.947
except she's French and,

01:04.947 --> 01:08.096
as you can see,
she's got enormous cans.

01:08.096 --> 01:09.660
<i>Enchant?</i>

01:11.465 --> 01:13.711
<i>Enchant?</i>

01:15.876 --> 01:17.120
(giggles)

01:17.120 --> 01:19.285
...I'd say you nailed it.

01:19.285 --> 01:21.091
I'll do you one better.

01:21.091 --> 01:22.995
You, sir,
got Stella thinking.

01:22.995 --> 01:25.502
"Gosh, Ted seemed
so cool today.

01:25.502 --> 01:27.077
Did I choose
the wrong guy?"

01:27.077 --> 01:29.854
Give it a week;
you'll get her back.

01:29.854 --> 01:31.016
And her front.

01:31.016 --> 01:32.290
(shudders):
Oh.

01:32.922 --> 01:33.894
Oh, did you just feel that?

01:33.894 --> 01:35.900
I think we just had
a "what up" quake.

01:37.303 --> 01:38.577
TED:
I don't want her back.

01:38.577 --> 01:40.582
Or her front.

01:40.582 --> 01:41.745
I just want to move on.

01:41.745 --> 01:43.419
And this was an important
step towards that.

01:43.419 --> 01:44.422
To moving on.

01:44.422 --> 01:46.126
(all murmur)

01:46.126 --> 01:48.102
<i>NARRATOR:
And you know,
I really meant it.</i>

01:48.102 --> 01:51.570
<i>But still, that night,
my mind began to wander.</i>

01:51.570 --> 01:53.215
(knocking on door)

01:53.215 --> 01:55.220
(harp glissando plays)

01:55.220 --> 01:56.855
I made a terrible mistake.

01:56.855 --> 01:57.857
I know.

01:57.857 --> 01:59.432
I'm a better person
than you are.

01:59.432 --> 02:00.695
You totally are.

02:00.695 --> 02:01.968
Let's get back together

02:01.968 --> 02:03.672
and have way more sex
than before.
Deal!

02:03.672 --> 02:05.849
(both moaning)

02:05.849 --> 02:08.155
(knocking on door)

02:13.870 --> 02:15.404
Hello, Ted.

02:16.537 --> 02:19.615
<font color="#ffff00">Captioning sponsored by</font>
<font color="#ffff00">20th CENTURY FOX TELEVISION</font>

02:19.615 --> 02:22.723
<font color="#ffff00">CBS </font>

02:22.723 --> 02:26.202
<font color="#ffff00">and VOLKSWAGEN.</font>
<font color="#ffff00">It's what the people want.</font>

02:29.270 --> 02:31.275
(sighs)

02:31.275 --> 02:33.382
No, come in. It's
not weird at all.

02:33.382 --> 02:36.390
Ted, Teddy Ted Ted Ted.

02:36.390 --> 02:37.632
(sighs)

02:37.632 --> 02:40.369
I knew it was wrong
to steal somebody's fianc?.

02:40.369 --> 02:42.345
I mean, I grappled with it.

02:42.345 --> 02:43.307
I was up nights.

02:43.307 --> 02:45.413
And not for the good reason.

02:45.413 --> 02:47.117
Well, sometimes
for the good reason.

02:47.117 --> 02:48.191
I mean, Stella and I

02:48.191 --> 02:49.764
hadn't seen each other
in five years,

02:49.764 --> 02:51.829
so, as you can imagine,
the beginning,

02:51.829 --> 02:53.805
it was just fast and furious.

02:53.805 --> 02:55.740
Lamps breaking,
furniture moving.

02:55.740 --> 02:56.783
You see this bald patch?

02:56.783 --> 02:57.715
Yeah, Tony...

02:57.715 --> 02:59.791
Anyway, we moved on.

02:59.791 --> 03:02.699
Me, Lucy, Stella--
we were gonna move to L.A.

03:02.699 --> 03:04.433
I was gonna become
a screenwriter.

03:05.205 --> 03:06.309
Then we bumped into you,

03:06.309 --> 03:09.947
and you just looked so... sad.

03:09.947 --> 03:11.221
Sad? No.

03:11.221 --> 03:13.928
I-I think what you're
calling sad was actually

03:13.928 --> 03:16.094
a jovial nonchalance.

03:16.094 --> 03:17.698
Ted, you looked awful, okay?

03:17.698 --> 03:19.904
Like a little dachshund puppy
with a bad back

03:19.904 --> 03:22.180
that's got to pull itself around
on a cart.

03:22.180 --> 03:23.153
Why are you here?

03:23.153 --> 03:25.388
Look, Ted,

03:25.388 --> 03:27.063
I know I can come across
pretty tough,

03:27.063 --> 03:29.770
but I can't bear to have hurt
someone the way I hurt you.

03:29.770 --> 03:31.474
I think fate put me

03:31.474 --> 03:33.681
on that corner
to make this right.

03:33.681 --> 03:36.217
Obviously, I can't fill
that giant crater

03:36.217 --> 03:37.751
that Stella left
in your heart.

03:37.751 --> 03:38.894
I've been dating.

03:38.894 --> 03:39.926
Like, a lot.

03:39.926 --> 03:41.060
And then I heard you got fired.

03:41.060 --> 03:42.934
I transitioned into
small business ownership.

03:42.934 --> 03:43.907
(clears throat)

03:43.907 --> 03:45.412
It's the backbone
of the economy.

03:45.412 --> 03:46.574
No, it's not.

03:46.574 --> 03:47.748
Ted,

03:47.748 --> 03:49.121
my family's got a lot of money.

03:49.121 --> 03:51.087
And I want to use that money

03:51.087 --> 03:52.590
to make this right with you.

03:53.092 --> 03:54.466
Tony is rich?

03:54.466 --> 03:55.939
Oh, Ted.

03:55.939 --> 03:59.709
Oh, Ted, tell me
he wrote you a check.

03:59.709 --> 04:02.055
Tell me he wrote you

04:02.055 --> 04:04.261
a big, fat check.

04:04.261 --> 04:05.494
A check so big

04:05.494 --> 04:07.369
it doesn't take its shirt off
when it goes swimming.

04:07.369 --> 04:09.505
(laughs)
Ha, that is a
big, fat check.

04:09.505 --> 04:11.681
A check so big, if
you had sex with it,

04:11.681 --> 04:12.945
you wouldn't tell
your buddies.

04:12.945 --> 04:14.889
That is a big, fat check.

04:14.889 --> 04:18.730
A check so big that when you sit
next to it on an airplane,

04:18.730 --> 04:19.902
you find yourself wondering

04:19.902 --> 04:21.637
whether the check should have
bought two seats.

04:21.637 --> 04:22.439
That...

04:22.439 --> 04:25.176
Is a big,
fat check!

04:25.176 --> 04:27.423
Yeah! He didn't
write me a check.

04:27.423 --> 04:29.087
Ted, I want to offer you a job.

04:29.087 --> 04:29.929
A job?

04:29.929 --> 04:31.093
Every year, my family gives

04:31.093 --> 04:32.867
a lot of money
to Columbia University,

04:32.867 --> 04:34.240
so I got some pull.

04:34.240 --> 04:35.203
How would you like

04:35.203 --> 04:36.747
to design...

04:36.747 --> 04:39.013
<i>NARRATOR:
My heart leapt into my throat.</i>

04:39.013 --> 04:40.016
<i>A new library?</i>

04:40.016 --> 04:41.018
<i>A new student center?</i>

04:41.018 --> 04:42.894
...your very own curriculum

04:42.894 --> 04:44.798
as a professor of architecture.

04:44.798 --> 04:46.102
(chuckles)

04:46.102 --> 04:47.104
Huh?

04:47.104 --> 04:48.278
No, thanks.

04:48.278 --> 04:51.546
What do you mean,
"No, thanks"?

04:51.546 --> 04:53.822
Ted, you would be

04:53.822 --> 04:56.158
a great professor, okay?

04:56.158 --> 04:59.036
You are knowledgeable,
you're a good talker,

04:59.036 --> 05:02.044
and when you need to,

05:02.044 --> 05:04.019
you can grow
a very handsome neck beard.

05:04.019 --> 05:04.981
(both laugh)

05:04.981 --> 05:06.626
I'm not gonna
be a professor.

05:06.626 --> 05:08.461
Teaching architecture is
what you do when your career

05:08.461 --> 05:10.837
has totally bottomed out and
you need to pay the bills.

05:10.837 --> 05:11.970
(all murmuring)

05:11.970 --> 05:13.373
Hey, hey, hey!

05:13.373 --> 05:14.507
Small business owner.

05:14.507 --> 05:15.650
Backbone of the economy.

05:15.650 --> 05:17.384
I'm not gonna take
that job, all right?

05:17.384 --> 05:18.558
I'm gonna be just fine.

05:18.558 --> 05:19.590
New topic.

05:19.590 --> 05:21.325
Okay, new topic.

05:21.325 --> 05:25.005
I just got a $200
speeding ticket today.

05:25.005 --> 05:26.338
Oh, that sucks, dude.

05:26.338 --> 05:27.581
You couldn't
talk your way out of it?

05:27.581 --> 05:29.486
You can't talk your
way out of a ticket.

05:29.486 --> 05:31.121
I've done it.

05:31.121 --> 05:32.795
It was-- what was it?--

05:32.795 --> 05:34.400
it was 1998.

05:34.400 --> 05:36.465
So where's the fire?

05:36.465 --> 05:38.109
There's no fire.

05:40.876 --> 05:42.621
Actually, uh,
you know, there is a fire

05:42.621 --> 05:43.924
at this barbecue I'm headed to.

05:43.924 --> 05:44.927
Nothing special.

05:44.927 --> 05:47.293
Burgers, ribs.... brats.

05:47.293 --> 05:51.344
Son, do you have any idea
how dangerous it is to be...

05:51.344 --> 05:53.550
Did you say brats?

05:53.550 --> 05:55.315
Yeah, brats.

05:55.315 --> 05:56.688
My mom marinates them

05:56.688 --> 05:58.693
in Belgian beer for two days.
No big.

05:58.693 --> 05:59.826
Funny thing was,
I could've

05:59.826 --> 06:03.807
sworn that one of those thick,
succulent,

06:03.807 --> 06:06.745
hickory-smoked brats
had some writing on it.

06:06.745 --> 06:08.218
Weird. Anyways,
what were you saying?

06:08.218 --> 06:09.823
What-what did it say?

06:09.823 --> 06:11.256
The brat?

06:11.256 --> 06:16.511
It said "Property of Minnesota
State Trooper Jorgensen."

06:16.511 --> 06:21.383
You a... you a brat man,
Officer Jorgensen?

06:23.759 --> 06:25.595
You going to this address?
Mm-hmm.

06:25.595 --> 06:26.797
Follow me and lean on the horn.

06:26.797 --> 06:28.503
We're gonna be running
some reds.

06:31.149 --> 06:32.613
Well, duh.

06:32.613 --> 06:33.786
I would've done that, too,

06:33.786 --> 06:35.922
if I'd have been going
to a barbecue.

06:35.922 --> 06:37.165
Damn, I was.

06:37.165 --> 06:39.070
See, it's all about
sizing up your opponent.

06:39.070 --> 06:41.235
I could tell that the officer
was a brat man

06:41.235 --> 06:43.111
because, well,
he was out of breath just from

06:43.111 --> 06:47.321
walking to my car and he had
mustard on his holster.

06:47.321 --> 06:49.498
Marshall Eriksen!

06:49.498 --> 06:52.606
Manipulating an officer
of the law with your sausage.

06:52.606 --> 06:54.039
MARSHALL:
Mm-hmm.
That is very hot.

06:54.039 --> 06:57.920
You think I can't talk
my way out of a ticket?!

06:58.421 --> 07:00.186
You think I can't

07:00.186 --> 07:02.130
talk my way out of a ticket?

07:02.130 --> 07:03.635
I am Barney
Stinson,

07:03.635 --> 07:06.141
master of manipulation.

07:06.141 --> 07:09.250
If I can talk a stripper
into paying me for a lap dance,

07:09.250 --> 07:11.616
I think I can talk
my way out of a ticket.

07:11.616 --> 07:14.022
Challenge accep-- Wait for it.

07:14.493 --> 07:15.998
(chuckles)

07:15.998 --> 07:17.872
I don't get it.

07:19.507 --> 07:21.582
Oh, "Ted."

07:21.582 --> 07:23.417
"Accep-Ted."

07:23.417 --> 07:24.450
I get it now.

07:24.450 --> 07:25.523
(knocking on door)

07:26.956 --> 07:28.060
What now?

07:28.060 --> 07:30.405
You want to be an architect?
Great.

07:30.405 --> 07:33.173
Guy I went to private school
with wants a new house built.

07:33.173 --> 07:34.517
Job's yours if you want it.

07:34.517 --> 07:37.053
Tony, look,
I don't need your help.

07:37.053 --> 07:38.557
Here's what he's offering you.

07:42.768 --> 07:45.475
That is a big, fat check.

07:52.223 --> 07:54.599
Showtime.

07:54.599 --> 07:56.073
License and
registration.

07:56.073 --> 07:57.477
Oh, of course, Officer.

07:57.477 --> 07:59.683
Right away.

08:03.593 --> 08:05.458
Sir, this is a gift certificate

08:05.458 --> 08:07.504
for a custom-tailored
Italian suit.

08:07.504 --> 08:10.040
So, we done here?

08:10.040 --> 08:12.276
$375!

08:12.276 --> 08:13.349
Ooh!
(chuckles):
Oh.

08:13.349 --> 08:14.682
