08:34.134 --> 08:35.778
And factual.

08:35.778 --> 08:37.613
License and regis...

08:37.613 --> 08:38.846
(sobbing)

08:38.846 --> 08:40.852
Oh, honey.

08:40.852 --> 08:43.529
Oh, no, no,
no, don't cry.

08:43.529 --> 08:45.604
It's okay. No
ticket for you.

08:45.604 --> 08:46.767
Oh.

08:46.767 --> 08:49.144
Just, uh, go a little
slower next time, okay?

08:49.144 --> 08:50.647
Yeah.
Okay.

08:53.986 --> 08:56.593
Thank you.

08:56.593 --> 08:58.468
Yeah!

08:58.468 --> 08:59.540
Excuse me.

08:59.540 --> 09:01.506
I think I left something
in New Jersey.

09:03.250 --> 09:04.284
Hey!

09:04.284 --> 09:06.118
How did your lunch go
with the rich guy?

09:06.118 --> 09:09.367
Well, uh, it started off great.

09:09.367 --> 09:11.332
<i>TED:
I want to design a house that</i>

09:11.332 --> 09:13.037
celebrates the landscape
without overpowering it.

09:13.037 --> 09:14.009
Mm.

09:14.009 --> 09:15.242
You know,
when Frank Lloyd Wright

09:15.242 --> 09:17.618
designed Fallingwater
in 1935, there's...

09:17.618 --> 09:19.323
Yes, yes, that's all fine.

09:19.323 --> 09:20.797
I'm sure you'll do a great job.

09:20.797 --> 09:23.063
What I'm really worried about
is the basement.

09:23.063 --> 09:24.968
Specifically the laundry room.

09:24.968 --> 09:26.242
The laundry room?

09:26.242 --> 09:30.151
I require a laundry room
of 15 feet by 15 feet,

09:30.151 --> 09:33.932
stain-proof ceramic tile
from floor to ceiling.

09:33.932 --> 09:36.338
I'm a man who likes to do
his own laundry,

09:36.338 --> 09:38.804
and sometimes, it gets messy.

09:38.804 --> 09:41.382
Messy?
Messy.

09:41.382 --> 09:43.718
Steel chains will dangle
from the ceiling

09:43.718 --> 09:45.221
at a height of nine feet.

09:45.221 --> 09:47.798
And that is where
my laundry bags

09:47.798 --> 09:50.736
will hang for three days
and three nights

09:50.736 --> 09:54.014
before I... clean them.

09:54.014 --> 09:56.992
Uh, Ted, it-it kind of
sounds like

09:56.992 --> 09:58.898
what this guy is asking you
to design...

09:58.898 --> 10:00.702
It's a murder house.
It is.

10:00.702 --> 10:02.066
It's totally a murder house.

10:02.066 --> 10:04.242
You know, as a
martial artist,

10:04.242 --> 10:06.146
I'm trained to
trust my instincts,

10:06.146 --> 10:10.829
and my instincts are saying
this... feels very good.

10:10.829 --> 10:13.436
The steak is so rare.

10:13.436 --> 10:14.970
(shudders)

10:14.970 --> 10:17.678
Right? Right?!

10:17.678 --> 10:21.216
One final concern:
soundproofing.

10:21.216 --> 10:25.398
I tend to make a lot of racket
when I launder.

10:25.398 --> 10:27.533
I'll show you what I mean.

10:27.533 --> 10:29.409
I'm gonna go to my laundry room,

10:29.409 --> 10:31.684
and you tell me
if you can hear me.

10:35.354 --> 10:36.898
Tony...

10:36.898 --> 10:38.802
does something feel off
about this guy?

10:38.802 --> 10:41.470
Yeah. Off the hook!

10:41.470 --> 10:43.475
Bro, you are
nailing this.

10:43.475 --> 10:44.979
(chain saw revving)

10:44.979 --> 10:46.684
(maniacal laughter)

10:46.684 --> 10:48.358
Ted, you can't design
a murder house!

10:48.358 --> 10:49.632
I'm not gonna design
a murder house.

10:49.632 --> 10:50.635
Ted, you can't design
a murder house!

10:50.635 --> 10:52.238
I'm not gonna design
a murder house!

10:53.902 --> 10:55.276
(engine accelerating)

10:55.276 --> 10:57.011
(siren blips)

10:57.652 --> 10:59.689
Bring it.

10:59.689 --> 11:02.325
Officer, please,
my wife is about to have a baby!

11:02.325 --> 11:03.327
Her water just broke!

11:03.327 --> 11:04.370
Where's your wife?

11:04.370 --> 11:05.775
She took the other car.

11:05.775 --> 11:09.614
This is Italian leather, so...

11:09.614 --> 11:13.053
I... Oh, come...

11:13.053 --> 11:15.229
I'm sorry about that
murder house thing.

11:15.229 --> 11:16.603
That was my bad.

11:16.603 --> 11:17.937
That's on me.

11:17.937 --> 11:19.069
So, new plan.

11:19.069 --> 11:21.546
You, my friend, are gonna build

11:21.546 --> 11:24.985
the Statue of Liberty a husband.

11:24.985 --> 11:27.461
Now, I got some suction
down at City Hall.

11:27.461 --> 11:28.464
Tony, stop it!

11:28.464 --> 11:29.868
I don't want your help, okay?

11:29.868 --> 11:31.101
You don't have to do this.

11:31.101 --> 11:32.505
Yes, I do.
Why?

11:32.505 --> 11:35.082
Because...

11:35.082 --> 11:38.992
when you were with Stella,
I know how much I missed her.

11:38.992 --> 11:41.328
I can only imagine you feel
the same way.

11:41.328 --> 11:44.035
(laughs)
Okay, well,

11:44.035 --> 11:46.682
let me put your mind a

11:46.682 --> 11:49.088
I don't want Stella back, okay?

11:49.088 --> 11:51.354
She lied to me
and left me at the altar.

11:51.354 --> 11:52.929
